An Arduino Diecimila outfitted with 
an ATmega168, programmed with RooCode 
(https://roocode.com), and incorporating 
the Mozzi library 
(https://sensorium.github.io/Mozzi/).

The instrument emits a basic tone, 
which can be filtered with the included 
potentiometer. However, the outdated 
Diecimila gets easily overwhelmed by its 
flashed program, and inevitably begins 
to glitch out and produce wonderful 
digital noise. The potentiometer then 
acts as a way to “fine tune” the noise, 
like cracking a safe. 
